## `pub fn mount(db: &Path, mountpoint: &Path, opts: MountOptions) -> Result<()>`
<!-- checksum: rust-fuse-3 -->

### Purpose
Convenience entry point. Opens the fs, constructs an `Adapter`, runs `fuser::mount2` (blocks until unmount).

### Implementation Notes

```rust
use fuser::MountOption;
use std::path::Path;

pub struct MountOptions {
    pub foreground: bool,     // ignored — fuser::mount2 always blocks; caller owns the thread
    pub readonly: bool,
    pub subdir: Option<String>,
    pub sync_mode: SyncMode,
    pub checkpoint_interval: Option<Duration>,
}

pub fn mount(db: &Path, mountpoint: &Path, opts: MountOptions) -> Result<()> {
    let fs = open_fs(db, OpenOptions {
        readonly: opts.readonly,
        sync_mode: opts.sync_mode,
        checkpoint_interval: opts.checkpoint_interval,
        ..Default::default()
    })?;
    let adapter = Adapter::new(fs);
    let mount_opts = vec![
        MountOption::FSName("sqlite-fs".into()),
        MountOption::DefaultPermissions,
    ];
    fuser::mount2(adapter, mountpoint, &mount_opts)
        .map_err(|e| Error::Sqlite(rusqlite::Error::ExecuteReturnedResults))?;
    // TODO: a better Error::Io variant for fuser errors.
    Ok(())
}
```

**Note for plan.rust.v2:** fuser's `io::Error` doesn't fit our `Error` enum cleanly. We should add `Error::Io(#[from] std::io::Error)` to the enum. Flagged.

